caption: I don’t know why it took me a long time to realize this place Reopened. It’s my favorite Thai food place in Boston. I was very upset when they closed down the original location, which is right around the corner.I’ll be making more Boston trips for my Thai food cravings 😋

Figured id get the Pad Thai since it's in the name...big mistake.  The chicken was mushy and the dish overall was too spicy. Pad thai is not supposed to be spicy. In fact, it's one of the more mild Thai dishes. This version of it was inedible. Hated it. Never again will I get food from here.
A little expensive for the quality, but the quantity is great. A strange pick up experience, with no one really even in the main dining area, but felt super safe with COVID and is open pretty late.
The food and service are great but their delivery service could be better.
One of the most authentic Thai in Boston. Many menu selections for Thais, the ones you usually don’t see outside of Thailand. Go for the boat noodle soup.

I've been here twice.  Both times the woman who takes the orders over the phone and cashes you out was extremely disrespectful.  I was planning on regularly ordering from here.  She shook her head multiple times in disapproval while interacting with me..  She also pretended not to speak English until I finally got her talking and suddenly she was able to speak perfectly.  disgusting behavior.

Last week was our first time we visited this place. But It is no doubt not the last. We passed a splendid evening with the good service, with the high quality  dishes and fine drinks and with the honest pay. We will absolutely visit there again.
My fav spot for quality thai food. I often meet people here to talk. The service was sociable and attentive.

After living in Thailand for just under 2 years, I’m always looking for solid Thai takeout. This pad Thai was the best I’ve had since leaving my province in Thailand!! We also ordered the panang curry. Very good meal and definitely have a new go-to Thai spot!
Delicious food. Ask for the yum nuah...the crispy chicken fried rice with basil...or the boat noodle soup. 😁 great prices.

price: super reasonable taste: good!

Good classic low-key Thai place; great for take out. Eating in the food is even better with no wait but it is definitely more of a small hole in the wall atmosphere. Highly recommend for lunch or a laid back meal. Food is on point.
This spot is good! Reasonable pricing, large portions and the staff are always very welcoming.
Really good pad thai and very large portions.
Not bad Thai
Always get my dinner here. Delicious and economical!
Awesome food, helpful employees, consistently great ambience. They charge affordable prices and the food quality is good. 5 stars.

caption: This spot has superb service as well as yummy meals. One of my favourite restaurants in the city. The meals served rapidly and the rates are reasonable. Recommended.

I used to love this restaurant and order from it every week but it’s getting worse and worse. Several times, my order has been delayed for more than an hour or sometimes even 2 hours. When I call to ask about the order, they were unnecessarily rude and said that I can’t cancel the order at all. This will be the last time I order from Pad Thai Cafe. Please save yourself the trouble and starved stomach.
Amazing place. Food is awesome, affordable, and generous portions. Would recommended the pad thai, mango curry and crispy chicken on rice. Speedy service and generally friendly staff!
Amazing Pad Thai!!

I wasn't blown away by the place, but my dish was good. The boat Noodle soup was spicy, delicious, and huge. It's not the best or the worst verison. It's worth a try. Not sure, about the pricing, I didn't pay.
so so
A nice cafe for quick bite of some Thailand style cuisines. Pad Thai was a bit salty, make sure you grab a cup of water near the door.
One of the best Thai restaurant in the city.
Great, authentic food

Authentic Thai food with good iced milk tea. I tried the mango curry chicken rice which was a really good portion drenched in curry. The chicken was a bit tough, but my Thai friend loves this store and came back 3 times in a week! The dry sukiyaki looked really nice.
Happen to come across this little gem. Recently spent 3 months in Thailand and this establishment was quite authentic from food to speaking Thai with staff. Would recommend any of their dishes!
Great Thai spot with loads of menu options, super tasty, friendly staff AND no added MSG, that’ll be five stars then 😬

Small but authentic! They have roughly 5 countertop window seats and 6 tables so being able to eat there is tricky. I food is legit and, if I lived in the area, I'd be there weekly!

So many great options and really great specials.  Also, they have nice chopsticks.  Definitely go here for a meal, it's a hidden gem.

Good, quick and pleasant.

OMG. This hidden gem is one of the more authentic Thai restaurants I've been to in a while. After reading the reviews I went with an idea of what to order ... good thing too as I don't speak Thai so I couldn't read one of their menus and I'm sure that's where the food is most authentic. I ordered the country (Thai) style Pad Thai and soon wished I had found this restaurant sooner. I rarely order Pad Thai at restaurants because it's not usually very good, but this dish made me a believer again. As the fact that it was served with the usual Thai hospitality and you have a winning combination.
Good Thai food. Taste really Thai very delicious
The food is not that good.

My favorite Thai restaurant of all time. Was taken here by a classmate over 20 years ago and when I crave Pad Thai, I come. Their Thai Style Pad Thai, not on the menu, is what I come for. I can’t find it anywhere else. 😋😋😋
Ordered mango friend rice. It had a deep burnt smell. When asked in counter they replaced it.

Pad Kee Map was the best I've had for the price. Reasonable cost, quick service, and a really good cozy hole in the wall feel. Highly recommend if you're looking for a quick bite without the usual upcharge for eating in the city

Good quick bite.  Quality in food varies from spectacular to mediocre. I have noticed a huge positive difference dining in vs. taking out.  The Massaman Curry is pretty good, and the Pad Thai is one of the best in the area.
A favorite for vegetarian comfort food
Food is served quickly. It's seat yourself and there aren't that many tables, but it doesn't usually take long to snag a table, at least not on weekday evenings.
Decent.

By far the best and most authentic Thai food I've had in a long time. Low prices, service at the counter but quick. Not a fancy place for sure, but one I highly recommend!
Stay away from their fried crispy duck. Decided to try their duck for the first time and got food poisoning. Never had any other problem before this with other dishes.
Very casual Thai hole in the wall with a good selection of mostly authentic Thai dishes. Service is efficient but friendly. Counter service only.

caption: Good Thai restaurant by the Thai people. You can expect the real test from Thailand ( mostly). Price is very affordable. The staffs are not that friendly. They don’t even like to talk to thai people like me. I found that weird. But we like it anyway because we love Thai food.
Excellent food

Not the best. Ordered seafood panang curry and received a huge plate of rice with a few pieces of seafood and veggies. I requested more curry sauce as I didn’t expect them to mix the curry and rice. I’m on the keto diet and a plate of rice was not acceptable. I was charged an addition $4 for curry sauce and told to order the dinner portion. Despite charging me dinner prices, I never received the dinner portion. Also, you have to clean your own plate so don’t add a tip. I ended up ruining my dress because I’m not used to cleaning my own plate at a restaurant. It was too late for me, I had already added the tip at check out. If you can find another Thai restaurant, I recommend trying there.

They've now reopened around the corner on Hemingway, still serving very good and affordable Thai food. The lack of visibility does seem to be hurting business, as each time I've been there it was very slow.

I get the Ka Prao and my partner enjoys the Pad Thai more than anywhere in Boston. We enjoy the casual service and the delicious food. We have tried other dishes every so often and are not let down by the flavors. Only downside is I feel the dishes are a bit overpriced for this level of service.
Great Thai food. Almost every item is delicious. The price is perfect for students

Can't be more happy for them to come back. There's probably a little disadvantage due to the corner location, but everything else remains the same. No other business within the same category (cafe style) can beat this place and Rod Dee's Thai authentic food.
